{
  "texts": [
    "◁Note that every world frame and powerset possibilization thereof (Example 2.9) is separative.Separativity can be characterized in other useful ways.Fact 4.6 (Separativity).",
    "For any poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩:1.",
    "⟨S, ⊑⟩ is separative iff for all y ∈ S, ↓y satisfies refinability, so ↓y ∈ RO(S, ⊑);2. if ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is separative, then for any x, y ∈ S, if x ̸ ⊑ y, then x and y are distinguishable by a set in RO(S, ⊑): ↓y ∈ RO(S, ⊑) and y ∈ ↓y but x ̸ ∈ ↓y.Proof.",
    "For part 1, refinability for ↓y says that if∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′: x ′′ ∈ ↓y, then x ∈ ↓y.",
    "But this is just to say that if ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′: x ′′ ⊑ y, then x ⊑ y, which is the non-trivial direction of separativity."
  ]
}